    '{
  "segments": [
    {
      "start_ms": 0,
      "end_ms": 6000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Good... Are you seeing any change in the way you and I have been talking and feeling since the first day you came here when we went?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 10000,
      "end_ms": 25000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah, definitely. I think that the first day I came here, I was just like... I''ve definitely come a long way since the first day I came here."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 27000,
      "end_ms": 29000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "You''ve done what? You''ve--"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 33000,
      "end_ms": 52000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "I''ve come a long way, I think. And I don''t really know why or how it happened. It makes sense that probably a lot had happened here in therapy. I don''t know. I feel like I was having way worse thoughts and way more grim outlook on the world. And even though right now I''m by no means feeling great, I''m definitely not as held up on everything."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 55000,
      "end_ms": 60500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "So you''re doing a lot better. You''re not quite sure why. It may have something to do with--"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 64000,
      "end_ms": 85500,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "I feel it in a weird way, I feel like I can come back just around the corner. I don''t feel OK about all the things that I didn''t feel OK about. It''s not like I solved all the things I was uncomfortable with. It''s just that I''m not focusing on them as much. I still think about them all the time. I''m just not dwelling on them as much as I did."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 88000,
      "end_ms": 92500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Well, let me give you some feedback about how I''ve been experiencing our sessions."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 94000,
      "end_ms": 96500,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah. That would be great."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 100000,
      "end_ms": 107000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "So here''s the way I experienced what''s been happening. In the first two, three sessions, I heard this story, a kind of puzzling story that you related to me, which was this-- sorry--"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 108000,
      "end_ms": 109000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "That''s OK."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 112000,
      "end_ms": 164000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "--which was this sudden experience of what you called an existential panic. And that sounded right. That''s what it sounded like. You were in New York. You suddenly were aware of the mass numbers of people, your insignificance, of the fact that everything was going to end, that everything was transient, that you would die, and along with everyone else. And it was terribly frightening to you. And it was even more puzzling as you described it to me because you had never experienced anything like this before."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 167000,
      "end_ms": 187000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "And furthermore, as I started to try to take some history from you in your first sessions, there was this puzzle that you had been extremely happy in your life. You''d had a very good life. And nothing bad had ever happened to you. So that was the way I got-- I"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 189000,
      "end_ms": 192000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Would agree with all that stuff."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 196000,
      "end_ms": 228000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "But then as I experience it, as we went along, things started to change in that way. You related to me that you never even had a fall off your bicycle, that you had good relationships with everyone. Your childhood had been perfect. And maybe that''s why this was scaring you so much because everything had been so perfect. But then over these last few sessions, other things started to come up as we talked. I began to get the feeling that you really weren''t that happy as a child."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 232000,
      "end_ms": 257000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "There were a lot of unhappy things going on, especially last week when we talked about this brace that you had to wear for three years, and how awful that was, and humiliating it was for you in gym class, and things like that. And then I''ve also-- we haven''t explored this in greater depth. But also, things were not always very happy at home, that your mother was pretty unhappy woman, and that she was pretty restrictive. And--"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 261000,
      "end_ms": 268000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "I think she was happy. She was just worried. I don''t know if unhappy is the word."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 270500,
      "end_ms": 276500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "If she hears a rustling outside in the yard and thinks that''s somebody is going to be dead, this sounds like she is not--"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 281000,
      "end_ms": 294000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "She isn''t really...It''s weird to me because like she really does worry a lot. But I would never in my life think of her as unhappy because she''s so happy. But she''s worried."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 297000,
      "end_ms": 303000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Yeah, well, being worried and being very happy at the same time, there''s some sort of dissonance there."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 307000,
      "end_ms": 311000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah, I agree with what you''re saying. But it''s so weird."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 314000,
      "end_ms": 319000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "But you must have seen that as a child and not quite known what to make of this."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 322000,
      "end_ms": 322500,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 327000,
      "end_ms": 350000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "And then that you''ve had fears before, the fear of flying, for example, which has always been extreme, which-- so my experience then is a progression from this idyllic life, idyllic childhood, gradually hearing more and more and more that it was more and more this stress. And I don''t know it you were discovering it now, or realizing it now, or those are things that you really didn''t know about, or didn''t want to talk about it, or-- so that''s puzzling to me."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 355000,
      "end_ms": 367000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Do you do you see this progression in our few talks of-- so the more we talk, the more it seemed there was some real unhappiness, more than you recognize at first in your younger life, the pain, the hypochondriasis, fears that you''ve had?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 373000,
      "end_ms": 391000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah. I definitely think that I would agree. But I think I knew it, that I was always-- I don''t know if I''m thinking of the word unhappy in the wrong way. But I agree. My whole life, hypochondriasis was a thing, for sure."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 394000,
      "end_ms": 397500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "That''s not the same as being a very happy child."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 402000,
      "end_ms": 423000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "That''s true. Yeah, that''s true. So then yeah. But then a lot of other things made me really happy. So it didn''t take over my happiness like it did with this most recent thing. This most recent thing was-- there''s no room for happiness because this was so like scary. Does that make sense?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 427000,
      "end_ms": 436000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "But it seems thought there''s some part of you that wants to perpetuate the idea, the myth maybe that you are an entirely happy person, and things have been very happy all through your life."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 441000,
      "end_ms": 443500,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Possible, I think you might be right."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 445500,
      "end_ms": 450500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "That''s going to get in your way in therapy, of course, because in therapy, you want to look very deeply into things."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 453000,
      "end_ms": 457000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "But the thing is, I don''t feel myself like trying to alter."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 458500,
      "end_ms": 461000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Oh, I don''t think you''re doing this."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 463000,
      "end_ms": 467000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "That''s the part. I feel like, how do I know in my head, I think."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 469500,
      "end_ms": 473500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Oh, right. I don''t think you''re doing this intentionally. It''s just this is the what I see as an outsider."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 476000,
      "end_ms": 480000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah, totally. So how do you figure that out if you don''t see it?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 483000,
      "end_ms": 498000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "It''s one of the reasons that we start to take a more careful history as well as take a look at some dreams, and daydreams that are going on. And the dreams that you''ve had are by in large not very happy dreams. There''s stuff going on in your own conscious that''s--"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 500000,
      "end_ms": 504000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Do a lot of people have really happy dreams all the time though?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 507000,
      "end_ms": 518000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "No. Well, they''re not necessarily happy dreams. But the dreams are often a way into what with the deeper thoughts are feeling. Any more thoughts about the two of us and how we''ve been doing and what''s been happening in our treatment?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 523000,
      "end_ms": 538000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah. I think that-- see, that''s what I was saying. I can pinpoint why I''m feeling better. But I know it has to be from coming into here, probably with some other stuff. But I don''t really know. I enjoy talking to you, and it''s helpful. But I don''t know how it''s helpful."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 541000,
      "end_ms": 550000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Yeah, yeah, yeah. Well, can you say more about how you''ve been experiencing out sessions, or questions you have of me, or thoughts that you''ve had, or the things we''ve talked about?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 556000,
      "end_ms": 592000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah. I think I''ve never really done much therapy. So going in, I didn''t really know what to expect. And I think I liked the way that you asked me questions of things that I probably would never think about as relevant. But then somehow they became relevant. So I liked that. And I liked that when I asked you about your ideas of death, and why you''re not scared of it, or all that stuff that you were open about it. And it was good to hear your perspective in that way."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 596000,
      "end_ms": 620000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "And like I totally hear it, and I agree with it. I just-- maybe more now, but not in the beginning-- it was hard for me to feel that way myself. So it''s not that I''m puzzled by how you''re all OK with it, everyone. I just don''t know how to do that. It''s still a blocker for me."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 625000,
      "end_ms": 641000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Yeah. Yeah. Well, there''s a difference between being totally oblivious of it, between that and being aware of death, know it''s there, have to cope with it, go on with life, try to get as much our life as you can, and then a continuum between those things, and then being very paralyzed."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 644000,
      "end_ms": 648000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Was there anger, harsh words between--"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 650000,
      "end_ms": 652000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah, definitely."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 654000,
      "end_ms": 658000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "I didn''t know about that. Tell me. Tell me about it."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 664000,
      "end_ms": 690000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "There were times when I was just angry, like why can''t I just go to the dance and sleep over at the house that everyone''s sleeping at? And I never ended up not being able to do it. But it was always like we have to work through it."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 693000,
      "end_ms": 698000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "But you say that in a pleasant way. Was it always so pleasant in your home when you were talking about this with your mother?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 704000,
      "end_ms": 728000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "It was always like. It wasn''t necessarily-- well, sometimes it got unpleasant. But it wasn''t less unpleasant as it was something to figure out. I always knew one way or another it would work out. But I knew I had to work through it."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 730500,
      "end_ms": 733500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Nobody really lost their temper."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 738000,
      "end_ms": 767000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "No, not really. But it was more of-- OK, I got the invite to the dance sleepover. And now I know my friends and I am going. I''m going to end up going. But I have to then work through it with my parents. And that was just a little-- an extra annoyance to me."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 770000,
      "end_ms": 776000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Was anybody getting angry or losing their temper, your brother, your father, your mother?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 780000,
      "end_ms": 783000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "I think sometimes my mom did, yeah."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 785000,
      "end_ms": 787000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "What was that like?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 791000,
      "end_ms": 793500,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "It was pretty scary."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 795500,
      "end_ms": 797500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Give me an example. Can you?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 802000,
      "end_ms": 805000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Gosh, if I can even remember."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 807000,
      "end_ms": 811000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Where are you? What year are you talking about when you say scary?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 817000,
      "end_ms": 831000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "When I was seven, eight. And maybe my brother did something bad, or lost-- I don''t know what he would have done, but she would yell at him maybe. And that I didn''t like seeing her so mad."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 833000,
      "end_ms": 835000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Yeah. He''d get punished?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 838000,
      "end_ms": 843000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Probably, yeah. Probably like to the corner or something, or not."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 847000,
      "end_ms": 852000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "I think it''s very hard for you to talk about negative things that happened in your family."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 858000,
      "end_ms": 883000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "I think so. But I think not even just in the family, I think in life. Yes. I have this-- whenever I talk about something negative, I have this feeling of like, but what about all the positive things? I feel almost guilty in a way, because like even not with a family, even if I talk about something negative like, then I think about what about-- how can I even-- there''s so much worse that it could have been."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 888000,
      "end_ms": 899000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Well, so I''m talking to you and getting some kind of history of your early life. As soon as you say something positive, negative, you''re feeling that oh, I''m going to believe now everything was negative, and you''ve got to reassure me that there were a lot of positive-- why would I think that?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 903000,
      "end_ms": 908000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "No, but I think it''s less for you and more for me, for my conscience in a way."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 910000,
      "end_ms": 912000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Conscience, you mean telling this."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 917000,
      "end_ms": 954000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Like knowing, telling, knowing that to myself-- let''s say I''m like, oh, yesterday sucked because I couldn''t work on a design because the internet was down. And that was a negative thing. But then I feel like I have to say like, oh, but I have a laptop that I own, and a home to do design work in. And I feel like I have to say that after because someone else would not-- why am I complaining? Basically, these are the things I feel like, I have to be--"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 958000,
      "end_ms": 964000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "But there''s a rule around here, floating around in your mind that maybe in the family too, you don''t get to complain."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 968000,
      "end_ms": 975000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "It''s not good to complain, I feel like, because I feel like I''m sitting here, and I''m breathing, and I''m living, and I''m OK."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 978000,
      "end_ms": 985000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "As soon as I say something negative, my mind goes to-- well, it could be worse, and think about the good things."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 989000,
      "end_ms": 995000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "So we could explore where that came from. Why is it so necessary to instantly say it could have been worse?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 999000,
      "end_ms": 1004000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Because I feel like then you could get really caught up on negative things."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1006000,
      "end_ms": 1008000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Who? Me or you?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1009500,
      "end_ms": 1010000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Me."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1011000,
      "end_ms": 1011500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "You."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1015000,
      "end_ms": 1022000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah. I can get really caught up on like-- I don''t like to be negative. I don''t like to look-- I''d rather look at the positive."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1024500,
      "end_ms": 1027500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "It we''re exploring this in a conversation or a therapy session--"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1029000,
      "end_ms": 1032000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah, that''s what you have to do is explore the negative."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1034500,
      "end_ms": 1042500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "You really have to do it. But you''re saying it''s quite hard. It''s really ingrained. There''s some sort of voice in you saying don''t talk about the bad things."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1046000,
      "end_ms": 1051000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah, or if you do talk about the bad things, don''t forget about the good ones."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1053000,
      "end_ms": 1058000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Yeah, right. And that''s what I think you''ve really got to work on in therapy in the future."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1060000,
      "end_ms": 1063000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah, I think that''s a good point."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1066000,
      "end_ms": 1073000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Yeah, you''re not going to be-- because that''s what happened with us. I thought, I''m baffled here. Here''s a girl who had an ideal childhood."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1077000,
      "end_ms": 1085000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "But I still think it was. I still think that there were bad things, negative things, but overall, ideal"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1086000,
      "end_ms": 1086500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1089000,
      "end_ms": 1096000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Because there could have been other worse negative things, and I''m OK."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1098500,
      "end_ms": 1102500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Sure. You could have been a slave in a galley pulling oars all day."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1105000,
      "end_ms": 1112000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "I could have, or I could have been abused, or I could have not-- or all lived in one bedroom, check to check."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1115500,
      "end_ms": 1121500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "But once again, you''ve got the strong message that you got to look at the bright side of things. You can''t complain."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1125000,
      "end_ms": 1129000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah, but I don''t think that''s wrong, is it, to look at the bright side of things?"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1132000,
      "end_ms": 1137000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "It is if you''re going to get involved in really examining yourself and your life in therapy."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1139500,
      "end_ms": 1142500,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "That''s true, because it''s about digging."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1146000,
      "end_ms": 1155000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Well, this is exactly what''s happened to us in our discussions. I''m left scratching my head every session. I''m just like, this doesn''t make sense. She''s never even fallen off a bike. Nothing that--"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1156500,
      "end_ms": 1157500,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "But I haven''t."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1159000,
      "end_ms": 1162000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "Well, I''m using it as a metaphor, that nothing--"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1164000,
      "end_ms": 1169000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "But I''ve never had surgery. I''ve never-- I''ve never--"
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1170500,
      "end_ms": 1173500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "See, I think you''re doing it again now."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1176000,
      "end_ms": 1178000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah, I think I am."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1182000,
      "end_ms": 1211000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "There can be a lot of pain in a family, a lot of unhappiness without there having to be major surgery, or manage your fall off a bike or whatever. It can be very subtle in a way. And this is not a kind of indictment of anybody, of your parents, or you, your brother. We''re interested really in what your experience is. And I think you conceal even almost from yourself what your experiences were."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1217000,
      "end_ms": 1225000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Or maybe also that I''m looking at it as every family has their things. Isn''t that just what family is? I don''t know. Maybe not."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1227500,
      "end_ms": 1229500,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "But we''re looking at your family now."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1231000,
      "end_ms": 1232000,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah, that''s true."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1235000,
      "end_ms": 1240000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
      "content": "But once again, you''re saying every family has their thing. It''s almost as though you''re a defense attorney."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1242500,
      "end_ms": 1244500,
      "speaker": "client",
      "content": "Yeah, I think you''re right."
    },
    {
      "start_ms": 1246000,
      "end_ms": 1250000,
      "speaker": "therapist",
